The paper focuses on clip localization in videos using natural language descriptions, which involves computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV and cs.CL are the most likely categories. The paper also proposes a bi-directional RNN with an attentive mechanism, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (AI) research. Hence, cs.AI is also a likely category. The paper deals with video content, which falls under the multimedia (MM) category. Finally, the paper proposes a hierarchical architecture that models video content with multiple granularities, which is a machine learning (LG) technique.
